# Data Definitions

## AWS Credentials — Required Before Any Athena or S3 Access

Credentials expire every **4 hours**. Before running any script or notebook that touches Athena or S3, refresh them:

```bash
source scripts/refresh_aws_credentials.sh
```

This sets:
- `AWS_ARTIFACT_TOKEN` — CodeArtifact token from `beehero` domain (us-east-1)
- `UV_INDEX_BEEHERO_PYPI_USERNAME` — `aws`
- `UV_INDEX_BEEHERO_PYPI_PASSWORD` — the token above

### Athena Connection Config

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| `S3_STAGING_DIR` | `s3://us-east-1-data-analytics-storage/athena-query-results/` |
| `REGION` | `us-east-1` |
| `WORKGROUP` | `data_analytics` |
| `CURATED_DATABASE` | `data_lake_curated_data` |
| `RAW_DATABASE` | `data_lake_raw_data` |

Use `source` (not `bash`) so the exports apply to your current shell session.

